      • detectSentences

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> detectSentences(AnnotatedText text,
                                                         java.lang.String... labels)
                                                  throws TalismaneException
        Detect sentences within an annotated text. Sentences are added in the form of an Annotation around a SentenceBoundary, with the start position (relative to the start of the annotated text) at the start of the sentence and the end position immediately after the end of the sentence.

        Sentence boundaries will not be detected within any annotation of type RawTextMarker.RawTextNoSentenceBreakMarker, nor will they be detected before or after the AnnotatedText.getAnalysisStart() and AnnotatedText.getAnalysisEnd() respectively.

        If the text contained existing SentenceBoundary annotations before analysis start, the first sentence will begin where the last existing annotation ended. Otherwise, the first boundary will begin at position 0.

        If the text's analysis end is equal to the text length, it is assumed that the text end is a sentence boundary. In this case, an additional sentence is added starting at the final detected boundary and ending at text end.
        Parameters:
        text - the annotated text in which we need to detect sentences.
        Returns:
        in addition to the annotations added, we return a List of integers marking the end position of each sentence boundary.
        Throws:
        TalismaneException
